She actually released two singles before she auditioned for The X Factor in 2012, singing “On My Knees.” During a recap of season two of The X Factor, the Huffington Post described her audition as one of the highlights of the season, stating that “it was a quiet but controlled performance, hitting some amazing grace notes.”

She then went on to become part of multi-platinum girl group Fifth Harmony with hits like “Sledgehammer”, “Worth It”, and “Work From Home” alongside members Normani Kordei, Lauren Jauregui, Dinah Jane Hansen, and formerly Camila Cabello.

Since she has become part of Fifth Harmony, american EDM duo Lost Kings featured Ally alongside A$AP Ferg on a track titled “Look At Us Now” released on the 9th of June, 2017. German producer Topic collaborated with Ally on a track titled “Perfect,” released the 26th of January of 2018.

On January 31, 2019, Ally released her debut solo single “Low Key” featuring rapper Tyga.

As of now, Ally has been working on her solo debut. She confirmed that she has 3 to 5 songs ready for it, including a feature. Ally also claimed she doesn’t have a name for the album/EP yet. It is set to be released around Fall 2019. The debut’s vibes are going to be “sultry” and “urban”, with other “fun flavors” as well.

description.plain:
“Low Key” Is the first solo single by the former Fifth Harmony member Ally Brooke and features the American rapper Tyga. The song is about Ally noticing a guy checking her out and acting confident about it:

It’s about a guy trying to talk to me and noticing me and I recognize that. I appreciate that, but I’m like ‘low key, low key, you should really get to know me’. I’m a really confident woman. I’m standing on my own and kinda saying: ‘hey, I’m really cool and I’m awesome. So, do you want to get to know me?’. It’s a really strong and empowering message and, honestly, I just want whoever hears the record to feel that exact same way.

Meanwhile, Tyga entices a girl with jewellery whilst also referencing his comeback and reinvention.

Ally has been working on this song since March 2018. In an interview to Chica, she revealed that the initial plan was to record a totally different song, but it never worked out. Then her manager called her and played her this song, which had been initially written for a male voice:

But I was like: no, this is totally meant for a female and this is meant for me. So we ended up changing it. I actually pitched up the key like two keys higher, then put my voice on it, my energy, my character and I’m so happy with the way that it turned out.

After Ally adjusted the song, Atlantic Records executives suggested adding Tyga to the mix. Ally was totally down for it, having had worked with the rapper already on Fifth Harmony’s “Like Mariah”.

description.plain:
“Lips Don’t Lie” is the second solo song by Ally Brooke featuring A Boogie wit da Hoodie. She promoted the song by sharing the track’s file on Apple Music and by teasing some lyrics on a Spotify playlist. She mentioned in an Instagram post that she first heard the song on August 2018 and recorded the song on October 29,2018.

In an interview to Radio Now, Ally claimed that she loved the song since the first time she heard and that it was recorded in October, 2018.

The title is likely a reference to Shakira’s 2005 hit “Hips Don’t Lie”. Ally is a big Shakira fan and one of her secret talents is singing like her:

“Fabulous” is a song recorded by American singer Ally Brooke. It was released by Atlantic Records on February 28, 2020, as a promotional single for Brooke’s then-upcoming debut English album. In the upbeat song, Brooke talks about finding and loving herself, despite any flaws, such as “curves and scars”. Its chorus contains an interpolation of Labelle’s song “Lady Marmalade”.

Brooke’s album was later shelved, and the singer is now expected to release her new debut album in 2024.

“Mi Música” is the lead single of Ally Brooke’s debut solo album, expected to be released in 2022. The song’s lyrics are entirely in Spanish, since Ally has Mexican descent, and the title translates to “my song” in English.

Despite being leaked in its entirety on September 30, 2021, the official release of the song was later announced by Ally Brooke on Twitter, on October 18, 2021.

description.plain:
[Español]

“Tequila” es el tercer sencillo de la cantante mexico-estadounidense Ally Brooke, de su próximo debut y primer álbum de estudio en español, Mi Música.

En el nuevo sencillo Ally Brooke habla sobre el amor propio, la importancia de reconectar con uno mismo y perseguir tus sueños incluso cuando no tienes la aprobación del resto de personas. La letra nos habla de las subidas y bajadas de una ruptura amorosa que terminan fortaleciendola.




[English]

“Tequila” is the third single by Mexican-American singer Ally Brooke from her upcoming debut and first Spanish studio album, Mi Música.

In the track, Ally Brooke talks about self-love, the importance of reconnecting with yourself and pursuing your dreams even when you don’t have the approval of other people. The lyrics tell us about the ups and downs of a love break that end up making her stronger.

description.plain:
Ally covered Jaci Velasquez’s “On My Knees” on her audition for The X Factor USA 2012.  She made it to the next phase of the competition and was eventually put in a girl group called Fifth Harmony.

The feedback from the judges was very positive. LA Reid noted that she had a “really special voice” and was “really impressed” by her. Demi told Ally that her voice “blew her away”, calling it special and beautiful. On the other hand, Britney said she was surprised, telling Ally that she should be on Broadway because her voice had a “theatrical dynamic”. Simon ended the feedback round by saying he had a feeling they were looking at “a future star”.
